
'''Pioneers of Change'''

URL = http://pioneersofchange.net/

The site has many interesting resources such as recommendations on social-change related books, podcasts, and movies/documentaries.

"Pioneers of Change is a global learning network of young people, in their 20's and 30's, who have committed to be themselves, do what matters, start now, engage with others, and never stop asking questions. The "pioneers" include social entrepreneurs, corporate and NGO professionals, civil servants, artists, teachers, and free agents from a variety of cultural and social backgrounds. Founded in 1999, Pioneers of Change today engages over 2000 participants in over 70 countries."

Carsten Ohm wrote us:

"One of the ways the P2P site is going to be peer to peer based, is that I am going to support a community of peers interested in using and sharing a simple dialogue tool using a Drupal site. But I hope and believe it will be able to qualify as P2P in other ways too. A process that I am looking forward to be part of - and be challenged and inspired by you and other peers." (2/2006)

